Package: analyzeeyedry
Title: Analyze Eye Movement Data Using Eyedry Algorithms
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Bernhard", "Angele", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "b.angele@bournemouth.ac.uk")
Description: Reads ASC files from EyeLink eye trackers and DA1 files produced by
    Robodoc.py, and computes fixation time measures using the exact computational
    algorithms from the eyedry program (Clifton, 1990). Produces gaze duration,
    total time, first fixation, regressions in/out, go-past time, and other
    standard reading time measures in a wide-format tibble compatible with the
    IXS output format. Includes both a single-call interface (analyze_eyedry)
    and a step-by-step workflow: extract_regions_from_script reads region
    boundaries from a delimited script file; asc_to_fixations converts an ASC
    file to a long-format fixation tibble; assign_regions_to_fixations assigns
    analysis regions to fixations; compute_fixation_measures calculates all
    standard reading-time measures.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    tibble
